e screen"},{"names":["--fullscreen","-fs"],"argument":"","description":"make the first frame fullscreen"},{"names":["--fullwidth","-fw"],"argument":"","description":"make the first frame wide as the screen"},{"names":["--maximized","-mm"],"argument":"","description":"make the first frame maximized"},{"names":["--geometry","-g"],"argument":"GEOMETRY","description":"window geometry"},{"names":["--no-bitmap-icon","-nbi"],"argument":"","description":"do not use picture of gnu for Emacs icon"},{"names":["--iconic"],"argument":"","description":"start Emacs in iconified state"},{"names":["--internal-border","-ib"],"argument":"WIDTH","description":"width between text and main border"},{"names":["--line-spacing","-lsp"],"argument":"PIXELS","description":"additional space to put between lines"},{"names":["--mouse-color","-ms"],"argument":"COLOR","description":"mouse cursor color in Emacs window"},{"names":["--name"],"argument":"NAME","description":"title for initial Emacs frame"},{"names":["--no-blinking-cursor","-nbc"],"argument":"","description":"disable blinking cursor"},{"names":["--reverse-video","-r","-rv"],"argument":"","description":"switch foreground and background"},{"names":["--title","-T"],"argument":"TITLE","description":"title for initial Emacs frame"},{"names":["--vertical-scroll-bars","-vb"],"argument":"","description":"enable vertical scroll bars"},{"names":["--xrm"],"argument":"XRESOURCES","description":"set additional X resources"},{"names":["--parent-id"],"argument":"XID","description":"set parent window"},{"names":["--help"],"argument":"","description":"display this help and exit"},{"names":["--version"],"argument":"","description":"output version information and exit"}],"version":"GNU Emacs 27.1","tldr":"> The extensible, customizable, self-documenting, real-time display editor.\n> See also `emacsclient`.\n> More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs>.\n\n- Start Emacs and open a file:\n\n`emacs {{path/to/file}}`\n\n- Open a file at a specified line number:\n\n`emacs +{{line_number}} {{path/to/file}}`\n\n- Run an Emacs Lisp file as a script:\n\n`emacs --script {{path/to/file.el}}`\n\n- Start Emacs in console mode (without an X window):\n\n`emacs --no-window-system`\n\n- Start an Emacs server in the background (accessible via `emacsclient`):\n\n`emacs --daemon`\n\n- Stop a running Emacs server and all its instances, asking for confirmation on unsaved files:\n\n`emacsclient --eval '(save-buffers-kill-emacs)'`\n\n- Save a file in Emacs:\n\n`Ctrl + X, Ctrl + S`\n\n- Quit Emacs:\n\n`Ctrl + X, Ctrl + C`\n"}
